IEC Chief Electoral Officer, Sy Mamabolo, has taken a jab at the media. He's accused journalists of focusing on isolated incidents and ignoring the commission's positive work. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - IEC Chief Electoral Officer Sy Mamabolo has taken a jab at the media. He said news organisations focused on isolated incidents ignoring the commission's positive work. READ: Results, so far, are untainted: IEC Mamabolo was speaking at the announcement of the final results at the IEC results centre in Pretoria. READ: IEC urgently investigating electoral irregularities "Distinguished media reports over the past few days have focused on a particularly negative discourse, highlighting isolated cases where our systems, process and people may not have worked perfectly. "But there's another discourse, a lesser-told story of 18 million voters who were assisted to vote honestly, quickly, and easily."